pageContext.collection_title: W. U. Audio Visual Services, Materials Library 72-18
pageContext.collection_description: This collection consists of 534 analog disc sound recordings spanning the years 1933 to 1968. Many of the sound recordings are original 16" transcription discs documenting Seattle area radio programs on KING, KIRO, KJR, KOMO, and KVI. Titles include "Hoover Commission Report," "Communism U.S. Brand," and "Your Arboretum."
